[
    {
        "content": "<p>Background: I'm trying to inject an extern crate for kernel crates to <a href=\"https://github.com/Artisan-Lab/tag-std/tree/main/safety-tool/safety-lib\">analyze unsafe Rust code</a>. Specifically, we want to directly write <code>#[safety::precond::Property]</code>without import safety_lib in each module.</p>\n<p>Safety_lib is no_std and able to work for kernel crates, but it must be compiled after <code>linux/rust/lib{core,compiler_builtins}.rmeta</code> is generated, and before other crates (like pin-init and kernel) compile. How to do this? <span aria-label=\"point left\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f448\" role=\"img\" title=\"point left\">:point_left:</span> This is my question.</p>\n<p>From <code>make help</code>, I see single file target is viable. It means I can build core and compiler_builtins first, and build others in the next command.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>$<span class=\"w\"> </span>make<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">help</span>\nRust<span class=\"w\"> </span>targets:\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>dir/file.<span class=\"o\">[</span>os<span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\">   </span>-<span class=\"w\"> </span>Build<span class=\"w\"> </span>specified<span class=\"w\"> </span>target<span class=\"w\"> </span>only\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But actually, it doesn't work:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">cat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">EOF</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">configs</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">ci</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span>\n<span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nothing</span>\n<span class=\"n\">EOF</span>\n\n<span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Merge</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">config</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"cp\">$(</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"cp\">$(</span><span class=\"n\">nproc</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rustavailable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">defconfig</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">ci</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">BUILD_TARGETS</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>\n\n<span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Build</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$BUILD_TARGETS</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The result is:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">No</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">Stop</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>If I only change it to <code>BUILD_TARGETS=rust/compiler_builtins.o</code>, the result is</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0725</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">feature</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">compiler_builtins</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">allowed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">features</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">compiler_builtins</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">23</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">12</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">23</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">#![feature(compiler_builtins)]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0463</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">can</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">find</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">note</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">aarch64</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">unknown</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">none</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">softfloat</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">may</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">be</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">installed</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">help</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">consider</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">downloading</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">rustup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">add</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">aarch64</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">unknown</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">none</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">softfloat</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">help</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">consider</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">building</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">standard</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">library</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">source</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">cargo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">build</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Zbuild</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The first compilation error can be solved by adding <code>,compiler_builtins</code> to rust_allowed_features in linux/scripts/Makefile.build.<br>\nBut second doesn't make sense, because I'm sure aarch64-unknown-none-softfloat is installed for this toolchain.</p>",
        "id": 528802558,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1752567029
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, you shouldn't add unstable features or try to build <code>core.o</code> as a single-target.</p>\n<p>What you want to do is modify <code>rust/Makefile</code> to mimic what is done for e.g. the <code>ffi</code> crate (which is one that goes after <code>compiler_builtins</code>).</p>\n<p>From a quick look though, you seem to need proc macros, <code>syn</code> and so on. If that is the case, then it will be more complex -- you can take a look at e.g. this prototype I wrote back then: <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/pull/1007\">https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/pull/1007</a>.</p>\n<p>I hope that helps -- good luck!</p>",
        "id": 528839464,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1752579483
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411477\">Miguel Ojeda</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/How.20to.20compile.20single.20file.20target.3F/near/528839464\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>What you want to do is modify <code>rust/Makefile</code> to mimic what is done for e.g. the <code>ffi</code> crate (which is one that goes after <code>compiler_builtins</code>).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Thank you, that's what I'm trying to do.</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411477\">Miguel Ojeda</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/How.20to.20compile.20single.20file.20target.3F/near/528839464\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>From a quick look though, you seem to need proc macros, <code>syn</code> and so on. If that is the case, then it will be more complex</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Actually, I've managed to make my safety_macro work on kernel crates, without pulling in any proc-macro related <em>source code</em>, but rather relying on rust binary libs.</p>\n<p>The idea is to precompile the proc macro to a <code>libsafety_macro.so</code>, and compile safety_lib based on <code>libsafety_macro.so</code>, core, and compiler_builtins to libsafety_lib.rlib. And then pass these dependencies flags through safety-tool-rfl a rustc wrapper</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">gh</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">zjp</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">CN</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">tag</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">safety</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">tool</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">safety</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">containing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">libsafety_macro</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">so</span>\n<span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"k\">extern</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">safety</span><span class=\"o\">=/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">gh</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">zjp</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">CN</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">tag</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">safety</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">tool</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">safety</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">libsafety_lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">some</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extra</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tool</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">attr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">flags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">well</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Zcrate</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">attr</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">feature</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">register_tool</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Zcrate</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">attr</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">register_tool</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">rapx</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>so <code>#[safety::precond::Property]</code> is just avaliable in each kernel crate module.</p>",
        "id": 528843269,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1752580809
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"931980\">Vague</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/How.20to.20compile.20single.20file.20target.3F/near/528843269\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Actually, I've managed to make my safety_macro work on kernel crates</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://artisan-lab.github.io/tag-std/pin_init/struct.ChainPinInit.html#method.__pinned_init\">https://artisan-lab.github.io/tag-std/pin_init/struct.ChainPinInit.html#method.__pinned_init</a> shows that result.<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/N1RUZvwgITuGPSjj0CA1y0yW/f067a8f6-b51d-4fd6-93d3-b6c787f85694.png\">/user_uploads/35136/N1RUZvwgITuGPSjj0CA1y0yW/f067a8f6-b51d-4fd6-93d3-b6c787f85694.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/N1RUZvwgITuGPSjj0CA1y0yW/f067a8f6-b51d-4fd6-93d3-b6c787f85694.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"1638x1011\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/35136/N1RUZvwgITuGPSjj0CA1y0yW/f067a8f6-b51d-4fd6-93d3-b6c787f85694.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"931980\">Vague</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/How.20to.20compile.20single.20file.20target.3F/near/528843269\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>compile safety_lib based on <code>libsafety_macro.so</code>, core, and compiler_builtins to libsafety_lib.rlib</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The reason to have extra safety_lib is only to allow writing a user-friendlier <code>#[safety::hazard::Pinned(slot, _)]</code>  syntax instead of  raw proc-macro form <code>#[safety::Hazard_Pinned(slot, _)]</code>. <br>\n(proc-macro crate doesn't offer access to an macro in nested module (i.e. only root items are able to be accessed) , so we have to restrucure these module paths in a normal crate.)</p>",
        "id": 528848686,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1752582533
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I made it by copying <code>safety.rs</code> from safety-lib to linux/rust, and add $(obj)/safety.o in rust/Makefile. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/os-checker/linux/commit/a2633ab780b9c548958bf7843a77721465afbcb9\">commit</a> on linux side, and <a href=\"https://github.com/os-checker/tag-std/commit/259f7790e05c9fa513ada03a3fe138ff7af6d588\">commit</a> on safety-tool side.</p>\n<p>The only weired thing is when I add safety.o to obj-$(CONFIG_RUST), <code>safety.rs</code> is never compiled.<br>\n(Also tried removing compiler_builtins.o from obj-$(CONFIG_RUST), and compiler_builtins was still compiled. So not sure where the magic comes from.)</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Diff\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"gd\">-obj-$(CONFIG_RUST) += core.o compiler_builtins.o ffi.o</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+obj-$(CONFIG_RUST) += core.o compiler_builtins.o ffi.o safety.o</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>To solve this, I have to put safety.o as a prerequisite of pin_init.o.</p>",
        "id": 528878529,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1752590725
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"931980\">Vague</span> has marked this topic as resolved.</p>",
